    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="1007"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1007">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.9421/49</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-25">April 25,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Japanese Ambassador called and stated that his Government was ready to enter
                    upon negotiations with this Government to bring about a treaty or convention
                    relating to consular functions somewhat along the order of certain conventions
                    this government had with other <pb facs="1165" n="1053" xml:id="pg_1053"/>
                    governments. I replied that I was interested in his suggestion and appreciated
                    his bringing up the subject; I added that I thought it had been mentioned
                    casually at least on one or two former occasions, to which he agreed. At his
                    further suggestion, I agreed to designate a suitable person in the Department to
                    confer with one of his counselors at the Japanese Embassy on the proposed
                    undertaking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ull</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
